sten, Kamerad, I am ready to give them and some twenty other liberalishki their freedom, if you agree to what you had practically agreed to yesterday. Such a small thing! The lives of twenty-four men are in your hands. If you say "no", they will be destroyed, if it is "aye", they live. Think, what marvellous power! You sign your name and twenty-two men and two women flock out into the sunlight. It is your last chance. Madamka, say yes!'

'Go to hell, you filthy Toad,' said Krug wearily.

